[[Griko]] or Grico is a language combining ancient Greek, Byzantine Greek and Italian. 

It is spoken in southern Italy and Sicily. 

It is called also in Greek "Katoitaliótika" - "Southern Italian" and Calabrian, after [[Calabria]], or Griko Salantino or Grecìa Salentina, after [[Salento]].

